{
  "local_port": 54944,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some interesting questions to ask yourself?",
  "response": "Asking yourself meaningful and thought-provoking questions can help you gain insight, foster personal growth, and deepen your understanding of yourself and the world. Here are some interesting questions to ask yourself:\n\n### Self-Reflection and Personal Growth\n1. What am I most passionate about, and how can I incorporate more of it into my life?\n2. What is one thing I\u2019ve been avoiding that I know would benefit me?\n3. What is a limiting belief I hold about myself, and how can I challenge it?\n4. What are my core values, and am I living in alignment with them?\n5. What would I do if I weren\u2019t afraid of failure or judgment?\n6. What lessons have my past mistakes taught me?\n7. What are my strengths, and how can I use them more effectively?\n8. Who inspires me the most, and what qualities do I admire in them?\n9. What does success truly mean to me, and am I chasing the right kind of success?\n10. What is one habit I want to develop or break, and why?\n\n### Relationships and Connections\n1. Who are the people who bring out the best in me, and how can I spend more time with them?\n2. Is there a relationship in my life that needs repair or closure?\n3. How can I be a better friend, partner# First attempt at overlays\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-15\nIt's hard because you have to get so much paint built up. On my 5th or 6th layer hopefully will be complete!\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581511\uff5c> 2014-02-15\nSweetness.I need to pick mine up\n>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-15\nNot many of us have em!!\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581510\uff5c> 2014-02-15\nI like how much the white stands out on the totally black scoops. I've got a Martini Racing theme on my other car that would lend itself nicely overlays on black scoops.\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-15\nOkay here is attempt 1 at painting the scoop, definitely won't be my last and I don't even know if I'll keep it this way but I'm just experimenting. What you guys think?\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581508\uff5c> 2014-02-17\nmy car is currently in the shop getting the key-mark removed from the whole left side. Lucky me.... But I aired out in the biggest (and probably the only) city around me where this could happen and I left the car over night for some drinks with friends, afterwards shopping and so on. So you can guess what happend. police said the car was parked the whole night so they couldn't really figure out what happend but many other cars where \"touched\" from a knife or something like that on their bodywork. I was lucky, I only found a 20inch line on the drivers door. But when I went to the police to write my statement and claim the car was \"stolen\" (for the insurance) they already found it due to my iPod dock that is in my glove compartment, it is locatable via Bluetooth. So I got my car back and saw the door. But then the bodyshop guy scatched around on it and the whole lower side of the car has to be repainted and polished again so you pay for the repaint because I tried to wrap it myself beforehand and you would have seen that. So this is what I did the day I got it back. I went on the totally other side and started to wrap the good side as well (the one I had not touched yet.) and wrapped it again because I wanted to do it for a long time if I took the \"stripe\" off. Now you would see when I stand next to my car. On the drivers side the lower side IS flat black from the door until the back wheel arc, on the other side (the non scratched side) it is \"gloss black\" because I did a two tone mixed wrap there. So it is like that only on one side, you can see the change clearly. I am not sure what to do. leave it (against the some shop guy better knowledge. leave it (against the some shop guy better knowledge), change the good side to flat black or make the flat black side to gloss black but then the whole car would need to be painted and it ended up being lower in value... hard decision), change the good side to flat black or make the flat black side to gloss black but then the whole car would need to be painted and it ended up being lower in value... hard decision\n\n\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-17\nWhat???\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581508\uff5c> 2014-02-17\na flat black wrapped lower body and a \"glossy\" (or \"simply\" painted) black upper body work is possible if you only do it on one side of the car, but you will see it clearly so I am not sure of I want to leave it like that (against the shop guys better knowledge) but finaly better the lower part in flat black than no lower part at all (but I will leave it visible or make the flat part \"glossy\" as well. but then I would have to repaint the whole car, and the paint is a \"less quality\" than the original so the cars value would lower. But then, it is my car, I do not want to sell it, so I should not be concerned about the value, shouldn't I) but finaly better the lower part in flat black than no lower part at all (but I will leave it visible or make the flat part \"glossy\" as well. but then I would have to repaint the whole car, and the paint is a \"less quality\" than the original so the cars value would lower. But then, it is my car, I do not want to sell it, so I should not be concerned about the value, shouldn't I\n>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-17\nLol I know but what i asked is what you think of my scoop.\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581508\uff5c> 2014-02-17\nsorry, completely missed that. Its very cool, especially the middle part that is like \"connected\" with the lower light covers. Very nice, so you went for \"sporty racing\" with it.\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581509\uff5c> 2014-02-17\nI like it Bumblebee\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581512\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nNot really digging the logo on the scoop, the lower section looks good though\nIf the scoop were the same \"no logo\" as the lower it would add to the lower section I think...\nGood job though\n>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nLOGO? It's part of the stipe design lol but I get you. I'm going to mess around with it another time.i just wanted to try it out.\n>>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581512\uff5c> 2014-02-23\nI know it is... My \"stipe design\" comment was based on you doing the whole thing. Good job man play around and repost...\n>>>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-23\nFair enough bro, will do!\n>>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581512\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nI know it is... My \"stipe design\" comment was based on you doing the whole thing. Good job man play around and repost...\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581509\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nthat aint a logo that's just part of the stripe.\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581512\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nGot what are ya saying but the whole thing would seem cleaner I think..\nEven if you put the stripe this far...\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nI'm not following you at all bro. This is the STIPE lol. I only did part of the stripe because the inlets are too high up, the tape would have to flex a lot in a curve to completely cover the gray. But that's an overlays job.\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581509\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nI think what he was tryin to say is I think it would llok better with out the tag on the stripe. But me I like it it dont say fast and the furious no where on it\n>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nTHANK YOU!!!\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581512\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nLol I guess if you know the context it makes sense\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-18\nHaha!\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581509\uff5c> 2014-02-23\nLooking better the more I see it.\n>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-02-23\nIt's growing on me too!\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-03-03\nUpdates:\n\nCustom vinyl overlay done on the tail light, doesn't distract drivers behind me and I didn't have to paint them! I will do the scoops like this eventually to change up the look:\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581510\uff5c> 2014-03-03\nAre those stickers or an overlay for the parking reflector? ... and please tell me it's not red\n> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581509\uff5c> 2014-03-03\nlooks sweet where did you get them and how much where they\n>> <\uff5cplace\u2581holder\u2581no\u2581507\uff5c> 2014-03-03\nCustom design from@Josh@PremiumAutoStyling.\n",
